(Abstract: AbstractThe epidermal growth factor receptor \(EGFR\) is a receptor tyrosine kinase) Tj
T*
(that is commonly upregulated in cancers such as in non-small-cell lung cancer, metastatic) Tj
T*
(colorectal cancer, glioblastoma, head and neck cancer, pancreatic cancer, and breast cancer.) Tj
T*
(Various mechanisms mediate the upregulation of EGFR activity, including common mutations and) Tj
T*
(truncations to its extracellular domain, such as in the EGFRvIII truncations, as well as to) Tj
T*
(its kinase domain, such as the L858R and T790M mutations, or the exon 19 truncation. These) Tj
T*
(EGFR aberrations over-activate downstream pro-oncogenic signaling pathways, including the RAS-) Tj
T*
(RAF-MEK-ERK MAPK and AKT-PI3K-mTOR pathways. These pathways then activate many biological) Tj
T*
(outputs that are beneficial to cancer cell proliferation, including their chronic initiation) Tj
T*
(and progression through the cell cycle. Here, we review the molecular mechanisms that regulate) Tj
T*
(EGFR signal transduction, including the EGFR structure and its mutations, ligand binding and) Tj
T*
(EGFR dimerization, as well as the signaling pathways that lead to G1 cell cycle progression.) Tj
T*
(We focus on the induction of CYCLIN D expression, CDK4/6 activation, and the repression of) Tj
T*
(cyclin-...) Tj
